<DESCRIPT>  BRIEF; PROFESSIONAL; BASEBALL  </DESCRIPT>
<LEADPARA>  Jack Clark equaled a career high by driving in seven runs, including three
with his 11th homer, as the host Boston Red Sox rolled to a 10-1 victory over
the Detroit Tigers on Friday.;    "I'm kind of a streaky hitter, and I get
games with home runs and RBIs in bunches," Clark said. "The bunches just
haven't been very often this season."  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  Sports  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  CLARK'S SEVEN RBIS KEY BOSTON  </HEADLINE>
<MEMO>  A.L. Roundup  </MEMO>
<TEXT>     Kevin Morton gave up five hits and struck out nine, becoming the first
Boston pitcher to throw a complete-game victory in his debut game since Don
Aase beat Milwaukee on July 28, 1977.;    Morton lost a bid to become the
first Boston pitcher to throw a shutout in his debut since Billy Rohr in 1967
as Cecil Fielder hit the first pitch in the seventh inning into the screen in
left-center field for his 21st homer and 65th RBI.; WHITE SOX 4, TWINS 2:
Robin Ventura's three-run homer in the seventh lifted host Chicago over
Minnesota as Jack McDowell (10-4) beat Jack Morris (11-6) in a battle of
All-Star pitchers.;    Minnesota has lost eight of its past 10 games. Chicago
has won 12 of 15.; RANGERS 8, ANGELS 0: In Arlington, Texas, Jose Guzman
outdueled Mark Langston for his third straight win as Texas trounced
California and jumped past the Angels into second place in the American League
West.;    Guzman (4-3) shut out California on three hits for six innings.;   
The Rangers raked Langston (12-3) for seven hits and seven runs in five
innings.; BLUE JAYS 2, MARINERS 1: Roberto Alomar's RBI double, his third hit
of the game, in the eighth inning gave Toronto the victory in Seattle.;
ORIOLES 7, YANKEES 4: Sam Horn and Randy Milligan homered as Baltimore ended
host New York's six-game winning streak.; BREWERS 4, INDIANS 2: Rookie first
baseman Reggie Jefferson committed a bases-loaded error, letting two runs
score and spoiling his first American League home run as Milwaukee beat host
Cleveland and ended a six-game losing streak.  </TEXT>
